      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that there was conflict, but some people argue that the nonviolent stuff was actually kind of a distraction or even a tool used by the government to keep things under control without actually fixing the deeper systemic stuff. do you think the mainstream history books mostly just focus on the nonviolent side because it's a cleaner narrative for the US?",
