      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a common academic critique that mainstream narratives often sanitize the complexity of the movement by foregrounding nonviolence. While the moral power of nonviolence was undeniable, critics rightly point out that it sometimes masked the deep, entrenched economic and systemic power structures that remained intact. Focusing heavily on nonviolent legal victories often creates a simplified narrative of a \"triumphant morality play\" rather than a messy, protracted struggle against entrenched power.",
